WEBVTT

00:02.750 --> 00:04.210
Previously on "Kevin (Probably)
Saves the World"...

00:04.210 --> 00:06.120
Reese: I wouldn't touch it!
[ Explosion, Kevin screaming ]

00:07.210 --> 00:09.250
I'm a messenger from God.
Oh, good.

00:09.250 --> 00:11.080
I'm here to guide
and protect you.

00:11.080 --> 00:12.210
Who are you talking to?

00:12.210 --> 00:13.580
She can't see me.

00:13.580 --> 00:16.880
In every generation,
there are 36 righteous souls.

00:16.880 --> 00:19.420
The only job you have in life
for the foreseeable future

00:19.420 --> 00:20.920
is to build up
your spiritual powers

00:20.920 --> 00:23.380
through acts of kindness
and selflessness.

00:23.380 --> 00:24.420
After you've done so,

00:24.420 --> 00:25.500
God is gonna show you

00:25.500 --> 00:27.120
how to find
the other righteous,

00:27.120 --> 00:29.170
and then you'll anoint them
with an embrace.

00:29.170 --> 00:30.620
Did that meteor
give you superpowers?

00:30.620 --> 00:32.330
Kevin:
Why would you even ask that?

00:32.330 --> 00:34.830
Because I've seen
weird stuff.

00:36.540 --> 00:38.380
That's my journal.

00:38.380 --> 00:41.830
When exactly were you gonna tell
me that you'd been arrested?

00:41.830 --> 00:43.120
♪♪

00:45.420 --> 00:48.460
You need to go upstairs,
pack your bags, and get out.

00:51.540 --> 00:53.460
It's time.

00:53.460 --> 00:54.750
Tell her.

00:54.750 --> 00:56.380
[ Breathes deeply ]

00:56.380 --> 00:57.880
Amy.

00:57.880 --> 01:01.920
I am the last
of the 36 righteous on Earth.

01:01.920 --> 01:04.790
What the hell
are you talking about?

01:04.790 --> 01:06.670
It's true, Amy.

01:06.670 --> 01:08.500
Oh, my God.

01:08.500 --> 01:10.250
Who are you?

01:10.250 --> 01:11.500
She's an angel.

01:11.500 --> 01:13.080
Angels are
a human construct.

01:13.080 --> 01:14.880
Let's just say...

01:14.880 --> 01:17.380
I'm a warrior for God.

01:17.380 --> 01:18.790
And so is Kevin.

01:18.790 --> 01:28.790
♪♪

01:28.790 --> 01:35.330
♪♪

01:35.330 --> 01:36.920
I don't see her.

01:36.920 --> 01:38.080
She's right there.

01:38.080 --> 01:39.170
Blue pantsuit.

01:39.170 --> 01:42.210
♪♪

01:42.210 --> 01:44.000
Jessica Yamamoto?

01:44.000 --> 01:45.000
Yes?

01:45.920 --> 01:48.080
[ Choir vocalizing ]

01:48.080 --> 01:50.170
One down.

01:50.170 --> 01:52.380
34 to go.

01:52.380 --> 01:55.500
♪♪

01:55.500 --> 01:56.960
[ Indistinct shouting ]
Man: Come on!

01:56.960 --> 01:58.500
Get him!

01:58.500 --> 01:59.920
Yeah!

01:59.920 --> 02:02.960
♪♪

02:02.960 --> 02:04.460
Man #2: Ooh!

02:04.460 --> 02:05.670
Woman: Come on!

02:05.670 --> 02:06.670
[ Grunting ]

02:06.670 --> 02:10.460
♪♪

02:10.460 --> 02:11.880
You die tonight!

02:11.880 --> 02:15.750
♪♪

02:15.750 --> 02:17.460
Man #3: Take him down!

02:17.460 --> 02:18.920
Whoo!

02:18.920 --> 02:21.790
[ Indistinct shouting ]

02:21.790 --> 02:29.540
♪♪

02:29.540 --> 02:30.580
[ Grunts ]

02:30.580 --> 02:31.790
[ Choir vocalizing ]

02:34.290 --> 02:37.790
All right, Kevin.
This is it.

02:37.790 --> 02:39.830
This is the last
of the 36 righteous.

02:39.830 --> 02:41.290
Are you ready?

02:41.290 --> 02:43.460
I've been ready for this
my whole life.

02:43.460 --> 02:53.460
♪♪

02:53.460 --> 03:03.330
♪♪

03:03.330 --> 03:06.040
Hello, Yuri.

03:06.040 --> 03:09.500
♪♪

03:09.500 --> 03:11.580
[ Cheers and applause ]

03:11.580 --> 03:13.250
You have done it, Kevin.

03:13.250 --> 03:16.330
You have saved the world.

03:16.330 --> 03:18.620
[ Fireworks exploding ]

03:18.620 --> 03:23.000
♪♪

03:23.000 --> 03:24.960
[ Sighs ]

03:24.960 --> 03:26.290
Thank you, Kevin.

03:26.290 --> 03:28.120
Now I can go home.

03:28.120 --> 03:30.460
Bye!

03:30.460 --> 03:32.210
Bye!

03:32.210 --> 03:34.330
Bye!

03:34.330 --> 03:36.330
Amy: Kevin.
Kevin.

03:36.330 --> 03:38.670
Kevin!

03:38.670 --> 03:40.500
Did you hear
anything I just said?

03:41.540 --> 03:44.040
Uh...

03:44.040 --> 03:46.620
Get. Out.

03:46.620 --> 03:53.420
♪♪

03:58.880 --> 04:01.790
Ahh! Yeah!

04:01.790 --> 04:03.670
Thanks for letting me
crash here.

04:03.670 --> 04:06.170
I just need to get out
of Amy's hair for a couple days.

04:06.170 --> 04:07.830
Ah, man,
are you kidding me?!

04:07.830 --> 04:08.880
[ Chuckles ]

04:08.880 --> 04:11.290
Welcome to...

04:11.290 --> 04:12.330
the Medina House.

04:12.330 --> 04:14.960
Ah! All right!
Eh?

04:16.580 --> 04:19.210
Wow, that is a big cage.

04:19.210 --> 04:21.620
[ Chuckles ]
That's Mr. Bungles' house!

04:21.620 --> 04:23.420
He's my ferret.

04:23.420 --> 04:25.540
Ferret?
Mm-hmm.

04:25.540 --> 04:27.250
Oh, he's not in there
right now.
Oh.

04:27.250 --> 04:29.000
Sometimes he goes
on these, like,

04:29.000 --> 04:30.750
adventures
around the house.

04:30.750 --> 04:31.960
Oh.
[ Chuckles ]

04:31.960 --> 04:33.210
Oh.

04:33.210 --> 04:35.080
It's been
a few weeks now.

04:35.080 --> 04:36.210
Great.

04:36.210 --> 04:38.380
Must be getting
hungry!

04:38.380 --> 04:41.080
Don't let your fingers hang
off the couch when you sleep.

04:41.080 --> 04:42.580
Yeah. [ Laughs ]
That's a good...

04:42.580 --> 04:45.250
Really.

04:45.250 --> 04:46.960
Don't.

04:46.960 --> 04:47.960
[ Mr. Bungles squeaks,
scampering ]

04:47.960 --> 04:49.290
[ Grunts ]

04:49.290 --> 04:51.330
[ Squeaking continues ]
[ Gasps ]

04:51.330 --> 04:53.620
♪♪

04:53.620 --> 04:55.920
[ Squeaking stops ]

04:55.920 --> 05:01.830
♪♪

05:01.830 --> 05:04.710
Yvette: You okay?
[ Gasps, sighs ]

05:04.710 --> 05:08.710
Yep, just making a giant rodent
doesn't gnaw my fingers off.

05:08.710 --> 05:11.170
No,
I mean with your sister.

05:11.170 --> 05:12.670
That fight seemed bad.

05:12.670 --> 05:14.880
Oh.
We've had worse.

05:14.880 --> 05:15.710
She'll get over it.

05:15.710 --> 05:17.790
Okay.

05:17.790 --> 05:19.170
As long
as it doesn't distract

05:19.170 --> 05:21.170
from whatever task
the Universe presents us.

05:21.170 --> 05:22.750
It won't.

05:22.750 --> 05:24.540
What you witnessed

05:24.540 --> 05:29.420
was the initial "white-hot
anger" phase of our fight.

05:29.420 --> 05:31.580
Any attempt at conversation
during this period

05:31.580 --> 05:33.330
would be a waste of time.

05:33.330 --> 05:37.210
Once she cools down,
the next phase will begin.

05:37.210 --> 05:38.330
The next phase?
Mm-hmm.

05:38.330 --> 05:40.460
I got a whole system
to deal with it.

05:40.460 --> 05:42.040
It always brings us
closer together.

05:42.040 --> 05:43.620
[ Chuckles ]
[ Breathes deeply ]

05:43.620 --> 05:45.750
I'll admit, the human capacity
for forgiveness

05:45.750 --> 05:46.880
is incredible.

05:46.880 --> 05:48.620
But still...

05:48.620 --> 05:51.330
Okay, look, look,
you're the expert at...

05:51.330 --> 05:52.620
[ Stammering ]

05:52.620 --> 05:54.580
You're the expert at whatever
you're the expert at.

05:54.580 --> 05:57.380
And I'm the expert at fighting
with my twin sister, okay?

05:57.380 --> 05:59.830
Just trust me.

05:59.830 --> 06:01.670
If you say so.

06:01.670 --> 06:02.960
[ Gasps ]

06:02.960 --> 06:04.750
Oh, my God.
What is that?

06:04.750 --> 06:06.920
Where? Where is it?
Where?

06:06.920 --> 06:09.170
[ Breathing heavily ]

06:09.170 --> 06:11.000
Was that a joke?

06:11.000 --> 06:12.790
Was that a joke?
That's real nice.

06:12.790 --> 06:18.460
♪♪

06:18.460 --> 06:19.830
Amy: Reese?

06:19.830 --> 06:26.040
♪♪

06:26.040 --> 06:27.880
Reese,
I know you're awake.

06:27.880 --> 06:29.540
You never sleep
on your side.

06:29.540 --> 06:35.380
♪♪

06:35.380 --> 06:37.880
Look, it's my job
to keep you safe.

06:37.880 --> 06:40.420
I was worried, and...

06:40.420 --> 06:44.790
well, it turns out I had
a right to be worried.

06:44.790 --> 06:48.250
I'm sorry
if that upset you.

06:48.250 --> 06:50.500
But I'm not sorry
about what I did.

06:52.620 --> 06:54.710
I hope
you understand that.

06:54.710 --> 07:02.580
♪♪

07:02.580 --> 07:05.210
I love you.

07:05.210 --> 07:15.210
♪♪

07:15.210 --> 07:20.000
♪♪

07:26.620 --> 07:28.880
[ Imitates
rooster crowing ]

07:28.880 --> 07:30.880
[ Gasps ]
Rise and shine, buddy!

07:30.880 --> 07:32.790
Ohh. Good morning.

07:32.790 --> 07:35.620
Mom's got breakfast going,
so I hope you're hungry.

07:35.620 --> 07:37.670
Ah. I am.

07:37.670 --> 07:39.500
I could eat a --

07:39.500 --> 07:40.540
Ah!

07:40.540 --> 07:42.620
That's bad-ass, man!

07:42.620 --> 07:44.750
You even sleep
for success.

07:44.750 --> 07:46.500
[ Chuckles nervously ]

07:46.500 --> 07:50.790
-Yeah.
-Ooh! Very dapper!

07:50.790 --> 07:52.670
Did the Universe
dress me?

07:52.670 --> 07:55.580
Oh.
Like a little Ken doll.

07:55.580 --> 07:57.460
Well, I'm not wearing this.

07:57.460 --> 08:00.040
The best part about getting
fired was no more monkey suit.

08:00.040 --> 08:01.120
Mm.

08:01.120 --> 08:07.330
♪♪

08:07.330 --> 08:08.790
[ Breathes sharply ]

08:08.790 --> 08:10.460
[ Sighs ]

08:13.250 --> 08:14.330
Great.

08:14.330 --> 08:16.210
[ Breathes deeply ]

08:16.210 --> 08:20.250
♪♪

08:20.250 --> 08:22.380
It's a job listing.

08:22.380 --> 08:24.330
"District marketing manager.

08:24.330 --> 08:25.830
Five years of experience.

08:25.830 --> 08:30.040
Working knowledge
of PowerPoint required."

08:30.040 --> 08:32.330
The Universe
wants me to get a job?

08:32.330 --> 08:35.120
I think it's about time.
Don't you?

08:35.120 --> 08:38.120
♪♪

08:41.580 --> 08:43.040
[ Whistling ]

08:43.040 --> 08:45.250
[ Horn honking ]

08:46.040 --> 08:47.670
[ Honking continues ]

08:47.670 --> 08:48.880
What the hell?

08:58.920 --> 09:02.380
You know, it's generally the
police who pull civilians over.

09:02.380 --> 09:04.790
Who the hell
do you think you are?

09:04.790 --> 09:06.120
Whoa. Slow down.

09:06.120 --> 09:08.000
Or what?
You'll arrest me?

09:08.000 --> 09:10.380
[ Scoffs ]
Like you arrested my daughter?

09:10.380 --> 09:12.420
[ Sighs ]

09:12.420 --> 09:13.750
Amy, I'm sorry.

09:13.750 --> 09:15.000
When were you planning
on telling me?

09:15.000 --> 09:16.460
On her second offense?

09:16.460 --> 09:18.170
I thought I was helping.

09:18.170 --> 09:19.330
Helping who?

09:19.330 --> 09:21.000
My brother
get away with a crime?

09:21.000 --> 09:23.170
No charges were filed.
That is --

09:23.170 --> 09:24.830
That doesn't make
a difference.

09:24.830 --> 09:27.120
You're right.

09:27.120 --> 09:29.080
I'm sorry.

09:29.080 --> 09:30.750
"I'm sorry."

09:32.620 --> 09:33.710
"I'm sorry."

09:33.710 --> 09:34.960
He's sorry!

09:34.960 --> 09:38.500
Your rear taillight's out.

09:38.500 --> 09:40.420
But I'm gonna
let that slide.

09:40.420 --> 09:45.330
♪♪

09:45.330 --> 09:46.620
[ Vehicle door closes ]

09:46.620 --> 09:49.210
[ Engine starts ]

09:49.210 --> 09:50.830
[ Vehicle departs ]

09:50.830 --> 09:52.170
Mm.

09:53.670 --> 09:56.710
[ Humming ]

09:56.710 --> 09:58.380
It's locked.

09:58.380 --> 09:59.830
They're not open
for another five minutes.

09:59.830 --> 10:01.580
Ah, thanks.

10:01.580 --> 10:04.250
[ Breathes deeply ]

10:04.250 --> 10:05.790
[ Chuckles ]

10:05.790 --> 10:07.710
Hey, that's a nice suit.

10:07.710 --> 10:10.500
Ah. You to--

10:10.500 --> 10:12.500
Bob Costas Collection?

10:12.500 --> 10:13.920
Yeah.

10:13.920 --> 10:15.500
Apparently so.

10:15.500 --> 10:17.920
How long
you been on the hunt?

10:17.920 --> 10:19.290
For a job? Oh.

10:19.290 --> 10:22.210
An hour and...
four minutes?

10:22.210 --> 10:23.880
[ Laughs ]
[ Laughs ]

10:23.880 --> 10:25.920
Oh, man.
You are a rookie.

10:25.920 --> 10:27.460
You -- You might as well
go get a cheese sandwich

10:27.460 --> 10:30.290
and save yourself some time,
'cause this job is mine!

10:30.290 --> 10:31.790
Okay.
Ho ho!

10:31.790 --> 10:32.830
Yes, I can feel it.

10:32.830 --> 10:35.790
It's mine!

10:35.790 --> 10:38.120
No.

10:38.120 --> 10:40.540
No, no, no,
no, no, no, no, no!

10:40.540 --> 10:41.830
I-It'll be okay.

10:41.830 --> 10:43.790
Oh, my God.
I...

10:43.790 --> 10:45.250
[ Groans ]

10:45.250 --> 10:47.250
You know, it --
it -- it doesn't matter.

10:47.250 --> 10:49.000
I wouldn't have got
this job anyway.

10:49.000 --> 10:50.250
Might as well
just sell the house...

10:50.250 --> 10:52.210
Wait. I think
I know what I'm here for.

10:52.210 --> 10:55.120
[ Chuckles ]

10:55.120 --> 10:56.210
Huh.

10:56.210 --> 10:59.290
♪♪

10:59.290 --> 11:00.710
Uh, I don't know
what to say, man.

11:00.710 --> 11:01.960
You are amazing.

11:01.960 --> 11:04.420
Just, uh,
nail the interview.

11:04.420 --> 11:06.540
And do it quickly,
'cause it's a little chilly.

11:06.540 --> 11:07.620
Okay, got it. Yeah.
Yeah.

11:07.620 --> 11:09.120
-M-My hair?
-Looks great.

11:09.120 --> 11:10.420
Good luck!
All right.

11:10.420 --> 11:12.120
I'll be in my truck!
Okay. Thanks, man.

11:12.120 --> 11:13.460
Thank you.

11:13.460 --> 11:22.120
♪♪

11:22.120 --> 11:24.540
[ Door rattling ]

11:24.540 --> 11:25.790
It's locked.

11:25.790 --> 11:27.540
And the keys are in the suit!

11:27.540 --> 11:29.380
Hi.

11:29.380 --> 11:30.790
Enjoyin' the day.

11:30.790 --> 11:35.830
♪♪

11:35.830 --> 11:37.620
[ Door rattling ]

11:39.290 --> 11:40.960
[ Siren chirping ]

11:40.960 --> 11:42.290
♪♪

11:47.170 --> 11:48.620
♪♪

11:48.620 --> 11:50.580
[ Engine shuts off ]

11:50.580 --> 11:53.790
♪♪

11:53.790 --> 11:55.330
Nate.
[ Chuckles nervously ]

11:55.330 --> 11:58.670
Got a call
about a naked loitering guy.

11:58.670 --> 12:00.330
So shocked it's you.

12:00.330 --> 12:04.710
Uh...I let someone borrow
my clothes for a job interview,

12:04.710 --> 12:06.620
and my car keys
were in the pocket.

12:06.620 --> 12:07.830
[ Chuckles ]
So...

12:07.830 --> 12:09.040
Yeah, I mean, you get it.

12:09.040 --> 12:10.670
Not even a little.

12:10.670 --> 12:12.920
Well, um,
I promise that it's true.

12:12.920 --> 12:14.920
And if you wait with me,
I'll prove it.

12:14.920 --> 12:16.040
Fine.
[ Sighs ]

12:16.040 --> 12:17.120
Okay.

12:17.120 --> 12:18.210
Whew!

12:20.380 --> 12:22.000
[ Sighs ]

12:22.000 --> 12:24.080
I've been wearing this new
brand of boxers lately, and --
Nope.

12:24.080 --> 12:25.120
Okay.

12:28.710 --> 12:31.120
Saw your sister.

12:31.120 --> 12:32.790
Yeah?

12:32.790 --> 12:34.540
She's real mad at me.

12:34.540 --> 12:36.830
At you? Why?

12:36.830 --> 12:40.500
I neglected to tell her
about arresting you and Reese.

12:40.500 --> 12:42.920
Oh. Right.

12:42.920 --> 12:45.830
Well, for what it's worth,

12:45.830 --> 12:48.040
I thought that was
really cool of you.

12:51.420 --> 12:54.880
Look, don't worry about it,
okay?

12:54.880 --> 12:57.620
She comes in real hot
when she's angry,

12:57.620 --> 12:59.460
but it -- it -- it fades.

12:59.460 --> 13:01.580
I hope so.

13:01.580 --> 13:03.080
It will.

13:03.080 --> 13:05.290
Sam! What happened?

13:05.290 --> 13:06.380
I-I...

13:06.380 --> 13:08.460
I completely tanked.
[ Groans ]

13:08.460 --> 13:10.960
But at least
I looked good failing, right?

13:10.960 --> 13:12.380
[ Chuckles ]
Ah.

13:12.380 --> 13:14.830
So, thanks for the suit.

13:14.830 --> 13:17.170
Yep.
Let's keep the public nudity
to a minimum here.

13:17.170 --> 13:18.790
Oh. Okay.

13:18.790 --> 13:21.080
Actually, do you mind
if I just grab my -- Thank you.

13:21.080 --> 13:23.330
My keys were -- See?
Keys, yeah.

13:23.330 --> 13:25.750
Sam, do not worry
about that job.

13:25.750 --> 13:27.500
We're gonna get you
a better one, all right?

13:27.500 --> 13:29.040
Come with me.
I have a plan.

13:29.040 --> 13:30.830
Uh, yeah.
Thank you.

13:30.830 --> 13:33.670
Okay. Let's go.

13:33.670 --> 13:35.790
Oh. Thank you.

13:35.790 --> 13:38.080
[ Breathes deeply ]
All right.

13:40.620 --> 13:43.210
Okay, before you say anything,
I am on the job.

13:43.210 --> 13:45.290
I am helping
that man find a job.

13:45.290 --> 13:46.960
I know.
I'm -- I'm just checking in.
Okay?

13:46.960 --> 13:49.040
[ Alarm beeping ]

13:49.040 --> 13:50.830
Okay.

13:50.830 --> 13:53.750
It has been 18 hours
since Amy kicked me out.

13:53.750 --> 13:55.960
Perfect.
How -- How is that perfect?

13:55.960 --> 13:59.120
Well, Amy's white-hot anger
has cooled

13:59.120 --> 14:01.710
to a sort of
white-warm anger.

14:01.710 --> 14:04.710
Phase two begins --
emojis.

14:04.710 --> 14:09.750
Little funny pictures that are
representations of emotions.

14:09.750 --> 14:11.580
I know what an emoji is.

14:11.580 --> 14:13.920
Well, this almost always works,
almost all the time.

14:13.920 --> 14:15.120
When I forgot
Reese's birthday,

14:15.120 --> 14:18.330
it was unicorn emoji,
poop emoji.

14:18.330 --> 14:20.080
And then when I forgot
Amy's birthday, it --

14:20.080 --> 14:21.080
Wait, wait, wait.
Wait, wait.

14:21.080 --> 14:22.420
You forgot Amy's birthday?

14:22.420 --> 14:23.960
Yup.

14:23.960 --> 14:26.000
It -- It's the same day
as your birthday.

14:26.000 --> 14:27.790
Um...yeah.
I was a jerk.

14:27.790 --> 14:28.790
Okay.
Okay?

14:28.790 --> 14:32.670
This --
This seems, uh...wrong.

14:32.670 --> 14:34.000
And dumb.

14:34.000 --> 14:36.960
Well, you're wrong...

14:36.960 --> 14:38.670
and dumb.

14:38.670 --> 14:41.170
Okay. But I suppose I'm gonna
have to trust your judgment.

14:41.170 --> 14:42.880
Yeah.
The more time I spend
on this plane,

14:42.880 --> 14:46.330
the more I realize
I do not understand humans.

14:46.330 --> 14:48.040
Mm.
I am right about this.

14:48.040 --> 14:49.120
You will see.
Mm...

14:49.120 --> 14:52.670
♪♪

14:52.670 --> 14:54.290
There you are.
Hey.

14:54.290 --> 14:56.080
Thanks.

14:56.080 --> 14:58.620
Okay. So, you are
in, um, marketing?

14:58.620 --> 14:59.960
Sales.
Sales.

14:59.960 --> 15:01.750
Actually, the same place
for 25 years.

15:01.750 --> 15:05.210
I mean, look at this.
Look at that résumé.

15:05.210 --> 15:07.210
There's one thing
on that résumé.

15:07.210 --> 15:08.880
Mm.

15:08.880 --> 15:10.880
This is very nice paper.

15:10.880 --> 15:13.420
Yeah. Yeah,
that's -- that's linen.

15:13.420 --> 15:15.460
Ooh.
Mm.

15:15.460 --> 15:17.000
Nobody does this anymore,
okay?
Oh!

15:17.000 --> 15:18.830
We need to modernize
your job search.

15:18.830 --> 15:22.040
Get you on job websites,
Cast as wide a net as possible.

15:22.040 --> 15:23.710
Lemme take a shot
at your new résumé tonight.

15:23.710 --> 15:26.330
Tomorrow
you'll be a new man.

15:26.330 --> 15:27.830
Wh-- Why --
Why are you doing this?

15:27.830 --> 15:29.170
You don't even know me.

15:29.170 --> 15:31.460
You need help.
I'm helping.

15:31.460 --> 15:34.670
Yeah, but...
people don't do that.

15:34.670 --> 15:36.710
I do.

15:36.710 --> 15:38.670
♪♪

15:38.670 --> 15:39.920
[ Knock on door ]

15:39.920 --> 15:41.750
Hi.
Hey.

15:41.750 --> 15:43.670
Uh, come in.
Thank you so much
for letting me crash here.

15:43.670 --> 15:46.040
Yeah.
[ Sighs ]

15:46.040 --> 15:48.290
I just -- I just couldn't
spend another night

15:48.290 --> 15:51.000
with Mr. Bungles
haunting my dreams.

15:51.000 --> 15:52.330
What?

15:52.330 --> 15:54.580
Oh, it's a, um...ferret.

15:54.580 --> 15:55.670
Oh.

15:55.670 --> 15:57.620
This isn't weird, right?
Me staying here?

15:57.620 --> 15:58.920
'Cause we're --
we're good and...

15:58.920 --> 16:00.460
No, no. It's not --
It's not weird at all, right?

16:00.460 --> 16:01.580
Yeah. Okay.
Okay, so...

16:01.580 --> 16:03.120
So, what should we do?

16:03.120 --> 16:05.540
Should we play cards,
order a pizza?

16:05.540 --> 16:07.380
Ooh! I saw
this video compilation

16:07.380 --> 16:09.790
of newscasters
fainting live on air.

16:09.790 --> 16:10.830
We should watch it
right now.

16:10.830 --> 16:12.830
It's so funny.
Uh...

16:12.830 --> 16:14.210
I'm going out to meet
someone for dinner,

16:14.210 --> 16:15.540
so you're kind of
on your own.

16:15.540 --> 16:17.210
[ Gasps ] Oh.

16:17.210 --> 16:18.500
Oh.

16:18.500 --> 16:21.710
Um...okay.

16:21.710 --> 16:23.830
It's nothing big.
It's ju-- It's -- It's...
Oh. No. That's great.

16:23.830 --> 16:25.670
That's great. You should be
meeting someone for dinner.

16:25.670 --> 16:27.040
I'm just -- Sorry.
I'm just gonna --
Oh.

16:27.040 --> 16:28.040
That was -- Okay.
[ Chuckles ]

16:28.040 --> 16:29.330
Yeah, no,
we all need dinner.

16:29.330 --> 16:31.420
It's -- It's
a delicious meal.
Oh. Oh.

16:31.420 --> 16:33.000
Well, have fun.

16:33.000 --> 16:34.710
And eat healthy.

16:34.710 --> 16:36.000
And good luck.

16:38.380 --> 16:39.580
Yeah.

16:39.580 --> 16:40.830
Uh...

16:40.830 --> 16:42.830
You're good, right?
I'm good, yeah.

16:42.830 --> 16:43.880
So...
I'll be here, yeah.

16:43.880 --> 16:44.880
Okay.

16:44.880 --> 16:45.880
[ Both chuckle ]

16:45.880 --> 16:47.580
[ Door closes ]

16:47.580 --> 16:49.040
♪♪

16:53.460 --> 16:55.420
Hey. Um...

16:55.420 --> 16:57.460
So, I was thinking about
doing some pizza tonight.

16:57.460 --> 17:00.330
Any topping requests?
Veggie?

17:00.330 --> 17:01.960
We could get crazy
and maybe, you know,

17:01.960 --> 17:02.830
throw some jalapeños
on there.

17:02.830 --> 17:04.290
Reese.

17:04.290 --> 17:06.040
Come on, you can't
stay mad at me forever.

17:06.040 --> 17:07.920
I'm pretty sure I can.

17:07.920 --> 17:10.420
Honestly, I don't know
what right you have

17:10.420 --> 17:12.420
to be angry with me
in the first place.

17:12.420 --> 17:15.830
I'm sorry.
What right I have?

17:15.830 --> 17:17.210
I trusted you.

17:17.210 --> 17:19.080
And you violated
my privacy.

17:19.080 --> 17:19.960
You live under my roof.

17:19.960 --> 17:21.380
Well, lucky me!

17:21.380 --> 17:22.750
You still have time
to kick me out,

17:22.750 --> 17:23.960
like you did with Kevin.

17:23.960 --> 17:26.250
He didn't even do
anything wrong.

17:26.250 --> 17:28.580
Wait. [ Scoffs ]
Reese, are you serious?

17:28.580 --> 17:30.880
He broke into a house
and had you playing lookout.

17:30.880 --> 17:32.500
That's not what happened!

17:32.500 --> 17:34.380
Okay, well, that's weird,
because Nate didn't correct me.

17:34.380 --> 17:36.040
You know what, Mom?

17:36.040 --> 17:37.790
Believe whatever you want,

17:37.790 --> 17:38.960
'cause I don't care.

17:38.960 --> 17:40.460
Neither do I!

17:40.460 --> 17:43.620
♪♪

17:43.620 --> 17:45.830
[ Sighs ]

17:45.830 --> 17:49.460
♪♪

17:49.460 --> 17:51.000
[ Breathes deeply ]

17:51.000 --> 17:52.380
Ahh.

17:52.380 --> 17:54.790
Still no reply from Amy.

17:54.790 --> 17:57.120
[ Breathes deeply]

17:57.120 --> 18:00.500
Maybe I hit her with the smiley
face with the gritted teeth?

18:00.500 --> 18:02.170
You know -- like
[Breathes sharply]

18:02.170 --> 18:03.210
"Sorry."

18:04.960 --> 18:06.750
Maybe.
You think that'll work?

18:06.750 --> 18:09.330
I mean...

18:09.330 --> 18:11.170
she's got to forgive me
eventually.

18:11.170 --> 18:12.580
Right?

18:14.710 --> 18:16.170
Kristin: So, yeah.
Um...

18:16.170 --> 18:17.500
Kristin's home.
[ Breathes sharply ]

18:17.500 --> 18:19.380
Well, you...

18:19.380 --> 18:21.080
Well, maybe we should just,
you know,

18:21.080 --> 18:22.250
check out her date...
Oh.

18:22.250 --> 18:23.710
...just to see if sh--
Kevin.

18:23.710 --> 18:25.120
Make sure that she...

18:25.120 --> 18:26.210
Man: Yeah.
Kristin: Yeah.

18:26.210 --> 18:27.290
Yeah, I'm sorry
about that.

18:27.290 --> 18:28.830
-[ Gasps ]
-Uh...

18:28.830 --> 18:30.170
Did she see me?

18:30.170 --> 18:31.250
Aah.

18:31.250 --> 18:32.380
[ Indistinct conversation ]

18:32.380 --> 18:33.880
No, no. You're good.
You're good.

18:33.880 --> 18:35.710
Okay.
Oh!

18:35.710 --> 18:37.170
He's handsome.

18:37.170 --> 18:38.880
He's not that handsome.

18:38.880 --> 18:40.120
Mm, he is.

18:40.120 --> 18:41.330
Just give me
a play-by-play.

18:41.330 --> 18:44.120
So, they're just talking.

18:44.120 --> 18:45.540
[ Chuckles ]
It was not good at all.

18:45.540 --> 18:46.460
Talking.
No. I still...

18:46.460 --> 18:47.460
Oh!

18:47.460 --> 18:48.710
What?

18:48.710 --> 18:49.880
...you know, cool.

18:49.880 --> 18:50.880
Now they're making out.

18:50.880 --> 18:52.460
No! Really?

18:52.460 --> 18:54.250
Gotcha. [ Laughs ]

18:54.250 --> 18:56.170
No, she's not into him.

18:56.170 --> 18:58.080
He's all looks,
no books.

18:58.080 --> 18:59.080
Oh, here she comes.
Here she comes.

19:01.000 --> 19:02.500
[ Yawns ]
Hi.

19:02.500 --> 19:04.750
Hey.

19:04.750 --> 19:05.920
How was your night?

19:05.920 --> 19:06.960
Uh, it was good.

19:06.960 --> 19:08.380
Good. Ohh.

19:08.380 --> 19:10.750
I just was...reading books.

19:13.170 --> 19:15.000
[ Breathes deeply ]
You know, if you wanted to,

19:15.000 --> 19:17.000
like, bring your date inside,
I could have --

19:17.000 --> 19:18.790
Oh, no, no.
No, it wasn't that good.

19:18.790 --> 19:21.670
Aw. Bummer.

19:21.670 --> 19:25.620
I don't do that,
you know.

19:25.620 --> 19:27.000
Mm.

19:27.000 --> 19:29.120
You and I the other night,
that was...

19:29.120 --> 19:31.750
that was an aberration
for me.

19:31.750 --> 19:33.620
Sure. I...

19:33.620 --> 19:34.960
I got it.

19:34.960 --> 19:37.540
You know what?
This is weird.

19:37.540 --> 19:39.750
It is so weird. But I'll be
out of here tomorrow.

19:39.750 --> 19:41.170
Okay, great.
Okay.

19:41.170 --> 19:43.880
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, and, hey,
you can close the curtains

19:43.880 --> 19:46.670
if you're done
looking out the window.

19:46.670 --> 19:48.170
Will do. Yes.

19:48.170 --> 19:49.710
Thank you for the couch.
Sleep well.

19:49.710 --> 19:53.000
Good night.
[ Door closes ]

19:53.000 --> 19:54.040
[ Pops lips ]

19:54.040 --> 19:56.790
♪♪

19:56.790 --> 19:59.710
Okay, open your eyes.

19:59.710 --> 20:01.710
Welcome to the new you.

20:01.710 --> 20:02.750
Wow!

20:02.750 --> 20:04.290
What is all this?

20:04.290 --> 20:05.750
Well, you held
five different positions

20:05.750 --> 20:07.040
at your old job,
so I just --

20:07.040 --> 20:09.210
I broke those out
into separate listings,

20:09.210 --> 20:10.540
and I-I beefed up
some other stuff.

20:10.540 --> 20:12.420
And...

20:12.420 --> 20:14.040
Oh.
...I set you up
on a jobs website.

20:14.040 --> 20:15.880
[ Chuckles ]

20:15.880 --> 20:18.120
Wh--
T-This is amazing.

20:18.120 --> 20:21.000
I've been at this so long
by myself,

20:21.000 --> 20:24.080
trying to support
my wife and kids, you know?

20:24.080 --> 20:26.000
To have someone
in my corner, it's...

20:27.460 --> 20:28.540
I just can't
thank you enough.

20:28.540 --> 20:29.790
[ Chuckles ]

20:29.790 --> 20:31.880
Well, thank me when
the offers start rolling in.

20:31.880 --> 20:32.880
[ Laughing ] Yeah.

20:32.880 --> 20:34.540
Okay, so...

20:34.540 --> 20:36.290
Ready?
[ Keyboard clacks ]

20:36.290 --> 20:37.710
There she goes.

20:37.710 --> 20:40.250
You just applied
to every job within 100 miles,

20:40.250 --> 20:43.250
and all of your contacts
got your updated résumé.
Wow.

20:45.040 --> 20:46.880
What?

20:46.880 --> 20:49.250
Yeah, that way, everyone
knows you're looking,

20:49.250 --> 20:51.120
and they'll be able to keep
an eye out for you, as well.
No, no.

20:51.120 --> 20:52.290
No. No, no, no, no.
Stop!

20:52.290 --> 20:53.420
Oh.
What's going on?

20:53.420 --> 20:55.040
Wh-- What am I gonna do?
I got...

20:55.040 --> 20:56.540
I got to leave.

20:56.540 --> 20:58.330
I-I-I got to go home.
-Why? Why? Why? Why?

20:58.330 --> 21:01.080
My wife does not know
I've been fired!

21:01.080 --> 21:02.620
[ Stammers ]
She's gonna kill me!

21:02.620 --> 21:04.790
♪♪

21:04.790 --> 21:06.710
[ Chuckles ]

21:06.710 --> 21:08.290
She's not actually gonna...
kill him.

21:12.830 --> 21:14.540
[ Tires screeching ]

21:14.540 --> 21:23.080
♪♪

21:23.080 --> 21:25.290
Sam? Hey.

21:25.290 --> 21:26.420
Got your stuff.

21:26.420 --> 21:27.830
Oh.

21:27.830 --> 21:29.830
Hey.
Yeah, thanks.

21:29.830 --> 21:31.000
What happened?

21:31.000 --> 21:33.170
Uh...

21:33.170 --> 21:35.830
Yeah, Tracy kicked me out.

21:35.830 --> 21:37.000
Because you lost your job?

21:37.000 --> 21:38.580
That's kind of harsh.

21:38.580 --> 21:42.670
Well, I-I've sort of been
laid off for a while, so...

21:42.670 --> 21:45.120
Oh. How -- How long?

21:45.120 --> 21:47.710
Oh. A year?

21:47.710 --> 21:49.330
You didn't tell your wife

21:49.330 --> 21:51.250
you've been unemployed
for a year?

21:51.250 --> 21:52.460
And a half.

21:52.460 --> 21:54.750
I think 18 months actually
might be more accurate.

21:54.750 --> 21:56.210
Oh, man.

21:56.210 --> 21:58.420
And I spent our entire
life savings covering it up.

21:58.420 --> 21:59.620
So that happened.

21:59.620 --> 22:01.330
Okay, now I want
to kick you out.

22:01.330 --> 22:02.880
I didn't want to worry her,
okay?

22:02.880 --> 22:04.960
I mean, I figured
if I got a gig,

22:04.960 --> 22:06.120
she wouldn't have
to get upset.

22:06.120 --> 22:09.250
But then three days
turned into three weeks,

22:09.250 --> 22:11.580
and then three months
and...

22:11.580 --> 22:14.580
Wait. How -- how did you even
keep up this big of a lie?

22:14.580 --> 22:18.000
Well, I'd get up at 6:00,
get ready for work as usual.

22:18.000 --> 22:21.880
I'd drive into "the office,"
which was the IKEA cafeteria.

22:21.880 --> 22:24.830
I'd look at the want ads,
eat the Swedish meatballs,

22:24.830 --> 22:26.080
and be home by 6:00.

22:26.080 --> 22:28.460
Wait.
Why -- Why do all this?

22:28.460 --> 22:29.670
I mean, lots of people
lose their jobs.

22:29.670 --> 22:30.670
I did.

22:30.670 --> 22:33.500
We had a deal.

22:33.500 --> 22:37.080
She would give up her career
to raise the kids,

22:37.080 --> 22:39.540
and I'd keep working,
and...

22:39.540 --> 22:42.210
She kept her part
of the bargain, and...

22:42.210 --> 22:45.500
if I can't keep up mine,
then...

22:45.500 --> 22:47.210
I'm worthless.

22:47.210 --> 22:49.040
[ Sighs ]

22:49.040 --> 22:53.750
I just realized I-I don't
where I'm sleeping tonight.

22:53.750 --> 22:55.000
[ Knock on door ]

22:55.000 --> 22:57.580
♪♪

22:57.580 --> 22:59.210
Kevin.

22:59.210 --> 23:00.710
Hey. Um...

23:00.710 --> 23:02.790
Listen,
I-I-I hate to do this,

23:02.790 --> 23:05.380
but can I crash
on your couch?

23:05.380 --> 23:07.710
Come in.

23:07.710 --> 23:10.080
[ Sighs ] And can Sam
crash on your couch, too?

23:10.080 --> 23:11.620
You remember Sam?
The guy I gave my suit to?
Hey.

23:11.620 --> 23:14.830
Hey.
-[ Sighing ] Yeah.

23:16.210 --> 23:18.540
Yeah. Hey.
Good.

23:18.540 --> 23:20.790
Do I smell nachos?

23:20.790 --> 23:22.290
Um...

23:22.290 --> 23:25.500
So, Nate,
this is a -- a sweet place.

23:25.500 --> 23:26.500
You just move in?

23:26.500 --> 23:27.880
Six months ago.

23:27.880 --> 23:29.790
Oh.

23:29.790 --> 23:32.790
Yeah, I let my ex keep
the furniture after we split.

23:32.790 --> 23:35.120
Sure, sure.

23:35.120 --> 23:38.500
And you're just...taking
the unpacking slow.

23:38.500 --> 23:39.960
Well...

23:39.960 --> 23:42.920
I only unpack something
when I need it.

23:42.920 --> 23:44.170
Ah. Nachos.
[ Chuckles ]

23:44.170 --> 23:45.170
Oh.

23:45.170 --> 23:47.420
All right.
Here we go.

23:47.420 --> 23:48.710
Ohh!

23:48.710 --> 23:49.960
Here. One to...

23:49.960 --> 23:52.540
Oh, no. I'm okay.
Yeah, thank you.
No? Okay.

23:52.540 --> 23:53.540
Wow.

23:53.540 --> 23:55.620
So...

23:55.620 --> 23:57.580
this is
what divorce looks like.

23:59.790 --> 24:00.960
Brutal.

24:03.080 --> 24:04.420
Um, you know what?

24:04.420 --> 24:06.920
Amy and I are this close
to patching things up,

24:06.920 --> 24:09.250
so I will be out of here
before you know it.

24:09.250 --> 24:10.380
Maybe even tonight.

24:10.380 --> 24:12.290
[ Chuckles ]
I might be a little longer.

24:12.290 --> 24:13.500
Just so...

24:13.500 --> 24:15.170
Hey, good luck.
[ Cellphone beeping ]

24:15.170 --> 24:16.330
I've never seen Amy
that mad.

24:16.330 --> 24:17.500
Yeah. Thanks.

24:17.500 --> 24:19.460
Hey! I got a hit!

24:19.460 --> 24:20.960
What?

24:20.960 --> 24:23.080
Yeah, yeah. On that --
that business website.

24:23.080 --> 24:24.500
I got an interview
tomorrow.

24:24.500 --> 24:26.380
Creative director
at an ad agency.

24:26.380 --> 24:27.540
Yeah.
Yes.

24:27.540 --> 24:30.420
Not exactly
my wheel of expertise,

24:30.420 --> 24:32.040
but they must have liked
something they saw

24:32.040 --> 24:33.170
in my new résumé,
huh?

24:33.170 --> 24:35.380
Kev, move.
Oh, sorry.

24:35.380 --> 24:36.710
Announcer: They weren't sure
he was gonna be able...

24:36.710 --> 24:38.210
...to play at practice...
Mmm.

24:38.210 --> 24:40.420
...let alone
that he'd show up tonight.

24:40.420 --> 24:43.960
♪♪

24:43.960 --> 24:46.290
Hello-o?

24:47.920 --> 24:50.080
Amy:
What do you want, Kevin?

24:50.080 --> 24:51.960
Rocky road.

24:51.960 --> 24:54.750
We're gonna talk until we get
to the bottom of this...

24:54.750 --> 24:57.120
or the bottom of this.

24:57.120 --> 24:58.170
No.

24:58.170 --> 24:59.960
I'm not doing this with you,
Kevin.

24:59.960 --> 25:01.420
We're not kids anymore.

25:01.420 --> 25:02.670
You can't fix this
with ice cream.

25:02.670 --> 25:04.500
Amy. Come on.

25:04.500 --> 25:06.540
You know that we're gonna get
through this eventually, so --

25:06.540 --> 25:09.120
I told you
that this would happen.

25:09.120 --> 25:11.750
I told you that I did not
want you pulling Reese

25:11.750 --> 25:13.000
into the tornado
that is your life,

25:13.000 --> 25:14.710
and look what happened.

25:14.710 --> 25:15.750
Exactly that.

25:15.750 --> 25:17.670
Okay, I would
never hurt Reese, okay?

25:17.670 --> 25:19.960
Please, Kevin.
You would hurt anyone if --

25:19.960 --> 25:21.210
If?

25:21.210 --> 25:23.170
Kevin, no.
Please, just -- just go.

25:23.170 --> 25:25.000
Just, please just go.
Look.

25:25.000 --> 25:27.670
I-I-I know it got crazy,
and I'm sorry, okay?

25:27.670 --> 25:30.330
But Reese and I
have gotten really close.

25:30.330 --> 25:31.790
And sometimes I think
it's easier for her

25:31.790 --> 25:34.830
to open up to me than --
than you.

25:34.830 --> 25:38.380
You barely knew her name
until a few weeks ago.

25:38.380 --> 25:40.880
That's...untrue.

25:40.880 --> 25:43.750
Do you remember when we went
to visit you when Reese was 12?

25:43.750 --> 25:45.420
She was so excited
to see you.

25:45.420 --> 25:46.880
And I was excited
to see her.

25:46.880 --> 25:49.830
Yeah, but not excited enough
to actually see her.

25:49.830 --> 25:51.250
I-I-I was working.

25:51.250 --> 25:52.750
Five days!

25:52.750 --> 25:56.830
Five days we sat in that
hotel room waiting for you.

25:56.830 --> 25:59.420
And we got a phone call --
"Hey, Aim, I'm sorry.

25:59.420 --> 26:01.830
I just got -- I got
super slammed at work."

26:01.830 --> 26:03.830
She was...

26:03.830 --> 26:07.210
She was so crushed, Kevin.

26:07.210 --> 26:08.670
I should have
written you off then!
I...

26:08.670 --> 26:10.290
I [Sighs]

26:10.290 --> 26:12.080
I'm a different person now.

26:12.080 --> 26:14.290
I wanted to believe
that, Kevin. I did.

26:14.290 --> 26:15.790
But it's never gonna happen.

26:15.790 --> 26:18.540
And I'm never gonna let you
hurt Reese like that again.

26:18.540 --> 26:22.120
So as much as it kills me,

26:22.120 --> 26:25.580
we have to move on.

26:25.580 --> 26:26.960
Without you.

26:26.960 --> 26:33.380
♪♪

26:33.380 --> 26:35.330
Uh, okay.

26:35.330 --> 26:37.620
I...

26:37.620 --> 26:40.380
I guess, uh...

26:40.380 --> 26:42.540
Okay.

26:42.540 --> 26:52.540
♪♪

26:52.540 --> 26:53.540
♪♪

26:53.540 --> 26:54.580
[ Door closes ]

26:54.580 --> 26:58.210
♪♪

27:02.170 --> 27:09.170
♪♪

27:09.170 --> 27:10.460
What are you doing here?

27:10.460 --> 27:11.670
I came to see you.

27:11.670 --> 27:14.250
Reese, no.
This is not a good idea.

27:14.250 --> 27:16.080
I heard you talking
to my mom.

27:16.080 --> 27:17.620
She's being totally insane.

27:17.620 --> 27:19.290
The worst thing
that we can do right now

27:19.290 --> 27:20.880
is talk
behind your mother's back.

27:20.880 --> 27:23.080
You know, she didn't even say
sorry for reading my journal.

27:23.080 --> 27:24.540
[ Sighs ]

27:24.540 --> 27:26.080
She was trying
to protect you, okay?

27:26.080 --> 27:27.120
And I don't blame her.

27:28.830 --> 27:31.380
You -- Go to school.

27:31.380 --> 27:32.580
Don't you have school?

27:32.580 --> 27:35.330
Okay.

27:35.330 --> 27:38.170
Well, ju-- You don't have
to be mad at me, too.

27:38.170 --> 27:39.710
No, I get it.

27:39.710 --> 27:42.330
Reese, come on.

27:42.330 --> 27:43.460
I'm ju--

27:45.540 --> 27:46.830
Reese.

27:46.830 --> 27:56.830
♪♪

27:56.830 --> 27:58.330
♪♪

27:58.330 --> 28:00.710
[ Sighs ]

28:00.710 --> 28:09.790
♪♪

28:09.790 --> 28:10.920
Oh!

28:10.920 --> 28:13.080
[ Breathes deeply ]

28:13.080 --> 28:15.330
Okay, I feel like
this should go without saying,

28:15.330 --> 28:17.750
but the bathroom
is private times for me.

28:17.750 --> 28:19.120
Cool?

28:19.120 --> 28:21.250
I take it the rocky road
wasn't a success.

28:21.250 --> 28:23.380
[ Sighs ]
No, it wasn't.

28:23.380 --> 28:26.500
But the good news is,
Sam's got a job interview,

28:26.500 --> 28:28.290
and I'll get him there
on time.

28:28.290 --> 28:30.290
I don't care about the job
right now.

28:30.290 --> 28:32.540
Uh [Chuckles] I don't
believe that for a second.

28:32.540 --> 28:34.420
That is
all you care about.

28:34.420 --> 28:35.710
You need to focus
on your family.

28:35.710 --> 28:37.080
The job can wait.

28:37.080 --> 28:39.380
Mm, no.

28:39.380 --> 28:40.920
That is
the exact wrong thing to do.

28:40.920 --> 28:42.790
I need to be all work
all the time

28:42.790 --> 28:45.080
until this whole thing
is over with.

28:45.080 --> 28:47.080
Eventually I'll find
the other 35 righteous,

28:47.080 --> 28:49.170
and then I'll deal
with Amy, and...

28:49.170 --> 28:51.250
Hopefully
we'll both still be alive.

28:51.250 --> 28:52.670
That won't work.

28:52.670 --> 28:54.040
That's the only thing
that will work.

28:54.040 --> 28:55.580
I can't tell Amy
the real story, right?

28:55.580 --> 28:56.830
Right.

28:56.830 --> 28:58.540
Okay. [ Spits ]

28:58.540 --> 29:02.120
So I'll just be the Universe's
tool until my job is done.

29:02.120 --> 29:04.000
Y-You can't do that,
Kevin.

29:04.000 --> 29:05.330
[ Chuckles ]
I did that for 15 years.

29:05.330 --> 29:06.500
I am great at that.

29:06.500 --> 29:09.080
I kept my head down,
I did a job that I despised,

29:09.080 --> 29:10.210
and I did it well.

29:10.210 --> 29:11.420
And how'd that turn out
for you?

29:14.170 --> 29:15.750
Not great, okay?

29:15.750 --> 29:17.500
But who cares?
This is what you want.

29:17.500 --> 29:19.460
Not one bit.

29:19.460 --> 29:21.290
Well, too bad.

29:21.290 --> 29:22.580
This is
what you're getting.

29:22.580 --> 29:25.500
So let's get to work.

29:25.500 --> 29:28.170
Look, Kevin,

29:28.170 --> 29:30.330
you need your family.

29:30.330 --> 29:31.620
I...

29:31.620 --> 29:33.500
[ Knock on door ]
Sam: Kevin?

29:33.500 --> 29:35.580
[ Sighs ]

29:35.580 --> 29:38.250
Excuse me.
I have work to do.

29:38.250 --> 29:39.880
I need a favor, man, okay?

29:39.880 --> 29:42.170
Oh, hey.

29:42.170 --> 29:44.040
Hey.

29:44.040 --> 29:45.580
I forgot my shoes.

29:45.580 --> 29:47.500
What?
Yeah, I left them
at the house.

29:47.500 --> 29:48.790
And I need them
for the interview.

29:48.790 --> 29:50.170
Tracy won't let me in,

29:50.170 --> 29:55.710
so do you think you could
pick them up for me?

29:55.710 --> 29:57.670
Please?
Please?

29:57.670 --> 29:58.920
Gladly.
I'm here to help.

29:58.920 --> 30:01.000
Ah! Man, thanks.

30:01.000 --> 30:02.040
Thanks a lot, man.
No problem.

30:02.040 --> 30:03.380
Okay.

30:05.000 --> 30:06.290
Tracy: I'm sorry.
Who are you?

30:06.290 --> 30:09.380
I'm a...a -- a friend
of your husband's.

30:09.380 --> 30:10.670
He has a big job interview

30:10.670 --> 30:15.080
and asked me to stop
and -- and get his shoes.

30:17.540 --> 30:19.790
Is he all right?

30:19.790 --> 30:24.380
He feels really bad and
wants to make things right.

30:24.380 --> 30:26.830
You probably think
I'm a terrible person.

30:26.830 --> 30:28.170
Me? No.

30:28.170 --> 30:29.920
I think --
I think you reacted

30:29.920 --> 30:32.120
exactly how a normal person
would react

30:32.120 --> 30:34.670
to being lied to
for a really long time.

30:34.670 --> 30:37.290
What's the job?

30:37.290 --> 30:39.920
It's an art director
at some ad firm.

30:39.920 --> 30:41.670
A little out of his field
of expertise, but...

30:41.670 --> 30:44.040
Um, a lot out of it.

30:44.040 --> 30:45.880
I was a graphic designer
before I had kids.

30:45.880 --> 30:47.670
Hm.
I can say without a doubt,

30:47.670 --> 30:50.170
Sam has the worst "eye"
in all of Texas.

30:50.170 --> 30:53.380
Well, uh,
he's trying at least.

30:53.380 --> 30:55.790
Maybe it'll --
Maybe it'll work out.

30:55.790 --> 30:58.750
I'll get you his shoes.

30:58.750 --> 31:00.670
Okay.

31:00.670 --> 31:02.420
Thank you very much.

31:04.790 --> 31:06.880
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

31:09.710 --> 31:11.460
Hey. Aim.

31:11.460 --> 31:12.880
Amy:
Is Reese with you?

31:12.880 --> 31:14.580
Um...no.
She stopped by earlier.

31:14.580 --> 31:15.880
When?

31:15.880 --> 31:17.040
This morning be--

31:17.040 --> 31:18.250
And then she left
for school.

31:18.250 --> 31:19.790
Well, she never showed up
to school.

31:19.790 --> 31:21.580
Oh. Um...

31:21.580 --> 31:23.040
Did you...
She's not answering her cell.

31:23.040 --> 31:24.710
I-I don't know what to do.

31:24.710 --> 31:26.670
Okay.
I'm -- I'm sure she's fine.

31:26.670 --> 31:28.380
[ Engine starts ]

31:28.380 --> 31:30.750
Okay.
I'm on my way, all right?

31:30.750 --> 31:32.920
♪♪

31:36.960 --> 31:40.170
Okay, thanks, Tyler.
Bye.

31:40.170 --> 31:41.500
[ Cellphone beeps ]
She's not at the diner.

31:41.500 --> 31:42.960
Look, in nearly
all these cases,

31:42.960 --> 31:45.710
the kid shows up
after a couple hours.

31:45.710 --> 31:49.330
Did you guys
have a fight?

31:49.330 --> 31:52.170
She got all angry
because I read her journal.

31:52.170 --> 31:54.790
Oh.

31:54.790 --> 31:56.920
I'm glad I did it.

31:56.920 --> 31:58.080
Because it's clear to me
that my brother

31:58.080 --> 31:59.500
should not be around Reese.

31:59.500 --> 32:00.750
Ever.

32:00.750 --> 32:02.960
Look, I'm sorry.

32:02.960 --> 32:04.540
I should have told you
about Kevin and Reese.

32:04.540 --> 32:07.210
But I think you're maybe
being a little harsh

32:07.210 --> 32:08.920
on your brother.

32:08.920 --> 32:11.170
It's just that I've seen him
actually give a stranger

32:11.170 --> 32:12.790
the clothes off his back.

32:12.790 --> 32:13.880
And from what I hear,

32:13.880 --> 32:15.040
he does that kind of thing
all the time.

32:15.040 --> 32:16.380
Great. Amazing.

32:16.380 --> 32:18.170
A mentally unstable
Mother Teresa.

32:18.170 --> 32:20.580
Look, I'm just saying,
he's not a bad guy.

32:20.580 --> 32:24.580
In his own weird way,
he's doing something good.

32:24.580 --> 32:25.790
[ Horn honking ]

32:27.880 --> 32:29.920
Oh, my God.
What is wrong with you people?

32:29.920 --> 32:31.460
[ Honking continues ]

32:31.460 --> 32:33.750
You know
you're not the police, right?

32:35.290 --> 32:37.710
[ Sighs ]

32:37.710 --> 32:40.750
♪♪

32:40.750 --> 32:41.830
[ Engine shuts off ]

32:44.080 --> 32:45.500
Hey.

32:45.500 --> 32:47.330
Okay, I drove past the park.
She wasn't there.

32:47.330 --> 32:48.880
Who was the last person
to see her?

32:48.880 --> 32:50.290
We think you were.
At Nate's place.

32:50.290 --> 32:51.830
Wait. How'd she know
you were there?

32:51.830 --> 32:54.080
I don't know. She always
seems to know where I a--

32:54.080 --> 32:56.790
[ Gasps ]
Wait. That app.

32:56.790 --> 32:58.880
She friended me on an app
so she could stalk me.

32:58.880 --> 33:01.120
What?
Or track me.
Follow me.

33:01.120 --> 33:02.290
It --
Not -- Not important.

33:02.290 --> 33:03.210
Anyway...
Well, can you track her?

33:03.210 --> 33:05.710
I think so.

33:05.710 --> 33:06.790
[ Beeping ]
Yep.

33:06.790 --> 33:08.040
Where is she?

33:08.040 --> 33:09.620
In the middle
of nowhere.

33:13.420 --> 33:15.670
There's her bike.

33:15.670 --> 33:16.920
Reese!

33:16.920 --> 33:17.960
Look at this place.

33:17.960 --> 33:20.000
It's disgusting.
-Are you kidding?

33:20.000 --> 33:22.500
I went to like 20 parties here
in high school.

33:22.500 --> 33:24.500
What?
What parties? I...

33:24.500 --> 33:25.960
I didn't go
to any parties.

33:25.960 --> 33:27.880
Didn't you?
The...

33:27.880 --> 33:29.790
Uh, anyway,
they weren't that fun.

33:29.790 --> 33:31.120
Um, let's split up.

33:31.120 --> 33:32.380
You go that way.
I'll go around back.

33:32.380 --> 33:35.210
-All right.
-Reese!

33:35.210 --> 33:36.250
Reese!

33:36.250 --> 33:39.420
♪♪

33:39.420 --> 33:40.580
Reese!

33:40.580 --> 33:43.040
Reese, where are you?!

33:43.040 --> 33:45.830
Reese!

33:45.830 --> 33:47.920
Reese?

33:47.920 --> 33:50.290
Amy: Reese?

33:50.290 --> 33:51.330
Kevin: Ree--

33:51.330 --> 33:53.420
Hey.

33:53.420 --> 33:54.750
Reese, get down here
right now.

33:54.750 --> 33:59.210
I'm not coming down.

33:59.210 --> 34:02.170
Reese,
what are you doing here?

34:02.170 --> 34:03.790
This is
where I come to think.

34:03.790 --> 34:05.290
You wouldn't know that

34:05.290 --> 34:07.420
because I didn't write it
in my journal.

34:07.420 --> 34:10.460
Okay, I-I should have
never done that.

34:10.460 --> 34:13.290
I promise you that
I will never break your trust

34:13.290 --> 34:15.120
like that again.
I'm sorry.

34:17.250 --> 34:18.880
I mean, I would've read it.
If it was me.

34:18.880 --> 34:20.120
Kevin, shut up.

34:20.120 --> 34:21.080
And you would've, too,
Reese.

34:21.080 --> 34:22.620
No, I wouldn't.
Mm-hmm.

34:22.620 --> 34:25.000
Just like I read Amy's diary
in fifth grade.

34:25.000 --> 34:26.670
What?
Don't get upset.
It was...

34:26.670 --> 34:28.250
It -- It was super boring.

34:28.250 --> 34:30.330
But, look,
I'm -- I'm sorry.

34:30.330 --> 34:33.080
I'm sorry
that I've been doing things

34:33.080 --> 34:34.380
that make you want
to follow me.

34:34.380 --> 34:36.580
And I'm sorry
that I've been keeping secrets.

34:36.580 --> 34:39.120
All -- All I ever wanted
was just to come home

34:39.120 --> 34:42.120
and live with
my older sister.

34:42.120 --> 34:44.120
Excu--
Two minutes older.

34:44.120 --> 34:45.710
Two minutes older.

34:45.710 --> 34:47.670
My much, much older sister.

34:47.670 --> 34:51.500
But I've been things like
the old Kevin used to do things.

34:51.500 --> 34:55.330
And I'm not --
I'm not the old Kevin anymore.

34:55.330 --> 34:57.290
The old Kevin
had a lot of cool things.

34:57.290 --> 34:59.380
He had a cool car
and a great apartment.

34:59.380 --> 35:02.330
But he didn't have
you guys.

35:02.330 --> 35:04.170
And I'm -- I am --
I'm talking in the third person.

35:04.170 --> 35:06.330
Yeah. A lot.
Right.

35:06.330 --> 35:09.670
I-I need you guys, though.
I really do.

35:09.670 --> 35:12.080
I-I-I can't do this
without you.

35:15.920 --> 35:17.710
Reese.

35:17.710 --> 35:19.580
Please,
just come down here.

35:19.580 --> 35:23.750
♪♪

35:23.750 --> 35:25.540
I have some demands.

35:25.540 --> 35:28.960
All right.

35:28.960 --> 35:31.710
You have to let Kevin
come home.

35:31.710 --> 35:34.380
Agreed.

35:34.380 --> 35:36.170
I can live with that.

35:38.790 --> 35:43.880
My stuff is my stuff.

35:43.880 --> 35:45.380
You can't come into my room

35:45.380 --> 35:48.500
or look at anything
without my permission.

35:48.500 --> 35:49.580
Agreed.

35:49.580 --> 35:50.710
[ Chuckles ]

35:52.170 --> 35:53.290
I want a dog.

35:53.290 --> 35:54.290
Reese...

35:54.290 --> 35:56.080
And I want my curfew
to be midnight.

35:56.080 --> 35:57.330
Whoa.
Oh, okay.

35:57.330 --> 35:59.170
Well, why don't you
enjoy living up here

35:59.170 --> 36:00.380
in this nasty warehouse?

36:00.380 --> 36:01.500
Okay, I'm coming.

36:03.420 --> 36:04.620
[ Grunts, screams ]

36:05.580 --> 36:06.710
Mom!
Hang on!

36:06.710 --> 36:07.920
[ Screams ]

36:07.920 --> 36:17.170
♪♪

36:17.170 --> 36:19.210
I don't understand.

36:19.210 --> 36:21.960
♪♪

36:21.960 --> 36:23.170
Reese.

36:26.790 --> 36:29.330
Let's, uh, go home.

36:29.330 --> 36:39.330
♪♪

36:39.330 --> 36:41.290
♪♪

36:46.500 --> 36:47.830
I'll just call Emma to see
what I missed at school.

36:47.830 --> 36:49.210
Good idea.

36:52.420 --> 36:54.080
[ Breathes deeply ]

36:57.580 --> 36:59.790
What? Forehead zit?

36:59.790 --> 37:01.540
How'd you do that?

37:01.540 --> 37:04.000
Do what?

37:04.000 --> 37:06.210
You were
10 feet away from Reese.

37:08.540 --> 37:10.080
Uh...

37:10.080 --> 37:12.080
Wh-- That's --
What are you talking about?

37:12.080 --> 37:15.170
I know what I saw.

37:15.170 --> 37:17.170
What?
What did you see?

37:17.170 --> 37:20.620
♪♪

37:20.620 --> 37:21.880
Nothing.

37:21.880 --> 37:23.580
I don't know.

37:23.580 --> 37:25.540
Okay.

37:25.540 --> 37:27.000
Hey, your shoes are muddy.
Hmm?

37:27.000 --> 37:28.750
Take them off.
[ Gasps ] Oh, no!

37:28.750 --> 37:30.750
Oh! Ah! Shoes!

37:30.750 --> 37:32.290
What?
Shoes!

37:32.290 --> 37:34.080
Okay, I-I'll be back.

37:34.080 --> 37:35.750
I ju-- It's the shoes.

37:39.830 --> 37:41.210
Kevin.
Oh, I'm sorry.

37:41.210 --> 37:42.250
Oh, no.
No, you don't have the sho--

37:42.250 --> 37:43.580
No, no, no. It's okay.
I can't get this job with...

37:43.580 --> 37:44.620
Tracy: Sam.

37:47.710 --> 37:48.920
Tracy. Wh--

37:48.920 --> 37:50.380
What are you doing here?

37:50.380 --> 37:52.710
I thought I might steal
this job from you.

37:52.710 --> 37:53.790
Wait. No.

37:53.790 --> 37:55.670
Tracy, that is
not our deal, okay?

37:55.670 --> 37:57.880
New deal.
Starting today.

37:57.880 --> 37:59.830
[ Sighs ] Great.

38:01.750 --> 38:04.000
My failure is complete.

38:04.000 --> 38:05.790
No, you can't think of it
like that.

38:05.790 --> 38:08.670
You guys were making the mistake
that I've been making.

38:08.670 --> 38:10.500
Doing the same thing
you've always done

38:10.500 --> 38:13.290
because it used to work,
but...

38:13.290 --> 38:15.500
sometimes
you gotta make a change.

38:18.460 --> 38:21.040
You know, the deal
wasn't that you work

38:21.040 --> 38:22.790
and take care
of me and the kids.

38:22.790 --> 38:24.710
I want this.

38:24.710 --> 38:26.420
I'm excited for this.

38:26.420 --> 38:27.750
Yeah?

38:27.750 --> 38:29.040
Are you Tracy?

38:29.040 --> 38:30.830
Yes.
Come on in.

38:30.830 --> 38:34.040
You guys would be crazy
not to hire her.

38:34.040 --> 38:35.750
Well, all right.
Good to know.

38:35.750 --> 38:43.500
♪♪

38:43.500 --> 38:45.210
Ah.
She looks pretty happy.

38:45.210 --> 38:46.040
[ Chuckles ] Yep.

38:48.380 --> 38:50.040
I'm gonna --
I'm gonna dry-clean this suit.

38:50.040 --> 38:51.290
I'll get it back to you
ASAP.

38:51.290 --> 38:52.880
Oh.
No, don't even worry about it.
Okay?

38:52.880 --> 38:54.580
You just -- You keep it.
[ Chuckles ]

38:54.580 --> 38:56.620
Thanks again.
Yeah.

38:56.620 --> 38:58.170
All right, man.
All right.

38:58.170 --> 38:59.420
[ Printer clicks ]

39:02.170 --> 39:04.830
Oh, hey,
this just fell...

39:04.830 --> 39:07.040
[ Printer clicking ]

39:07.040 --> 39:12.920
♪♪

39:12.920 --> 39:15.080
[ Gasping ]

39:15.080 --> 39:25.080
♪♪

39:25.080 --> 39:32.960
♪♪

39:32.960 --> 39:34.710
[ Clears throat ]
I wanna clarify something.

39:34.710 --> 39:38.040
What is your job again?

39:38.040 --> 39:40.040
My -- My job?

39:40.040 --> 39:42.210
Yeah, it's to protect me,
right?

39:42.210 --> 39:43.710
That's what you're
supposed to do?

39:43.710 --> 39:45.000
Where are
you going with this, Kevin?

39:45.000 --> 39:46.080
Well, I'm wondering
if I'm on, like,

39:46.080 --> 39:48.120
a friends-and-family plan.

39:48.120 --> 39:51.460
Like, unlimited rescues
for me and my family members.

39:51.460 --> 39:54.080
Do you have a problem
with something I did?

39:54.080 --> 39:55.960
No.
I just wanna understand.

39:55.960 --> 40:00.210
Because you came really close
to revealing yourself.

40:00.210 --> 40:02.790
I'm here to make sure
you do your job.

40:02.790 --> 40:04.170
That's all.

40:04.170 --> 40:06.710
And you seem most effective
when you're with your family.

40:06.710 --> 40:09.750
So as far as I'm concerned,
I've done my part.

40:09.750 --> 40:11.620
Now, are you doing yours?

40:11.620 --> 40:16.580
Well, I think
I had a vision.

40:16.580 --> 40:19.080
But it was different.

40:19.080 --> 40:20.380
I just got these, like...

40:22.080 --> 40:23.170
Aah!

40:25.580 --> 40:26.750
That's all the things
I've seen so far.

40:26.750 --> 40:27.830
[ Clears throat ]

40:27.830 --> 40:29.500
How...

40:29.500 --> 40:30.750
Right.

40:33.960 --> 40:37.750
Hey, who even took
this picture?

40:37.750 --> 40:39.710
That's so weird.

40:39.710 --> 40:42.500
Oh, you -- you
never told me about this.

40:42.500 --> 40:45.380
I've never been there.
That is completely new.

40:45.380 --> 40:47.330
Oh, we have to find out
where this is.

40:47.330 --> 40:48.830
That's where you'll find
the next righteous person.

